<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-title>Swift on Server Newsletter</mj-title>
    <mj-preview>Pre-header Text</mj-preview>
    <mj-attributes>
      <mj-all
        font-family="'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"
      ></mj-all>
      <mj-text
        font-weight="400"
        font-size="16px"
        color="#000000"
        line-height="24px"
        font-family="'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"
      ></mj-text>
    </mj-attributes>
    <mj-style inline="inline">
      .body-section { -webkit-box-shadow: 1px 4px 11px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
      -moz-box-shadow: 1px 4px 11px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15); box-shadow: 1px 4px
      11px 0px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15); }
    </mj-style>
    <mj-style inline="inline">
      .text-link, a { color: inherit; }
    </mj-style>
    <mj-style inline="inline"> .footer-link { color: #888888 } </mj-style>
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#ffffff" width="600px">
    <mj-section full-width="full-width" padding-bottom="0">
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-image
          src="https://swiftonserver.com/images/logos/logo.png"
          width="100px"
          alt="Swift on Server Logo"
          padding="0"
          href="https://swiftonserver.com"
          padding-bottom="20px"
        />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section background-color="#5856D7">
      <mj-column padding="20px">
        <mj-text color="#ffffff" font-size="32px" align="center">
          Swift on Server
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-wrapper padding-top="0" padding-bottom="0" css-class="body-section">
      <mj-section
        background-color="#fcfcfc"
        padding-left="15px"
        padding-right="15px"
      >
        <mj-column width="100%">
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            Dear subscriber,<br />
            <br />
            I'm excited to announce an update to your newsletter subscription. You're now subscribed to <a href="https://swiftonserver.com">swiftonserver.com</a>, replacing the original <a href="https://theswiftdev.com">theswiftdev.com</a> newsletter.<br />
            <br />
            Our brand new newsletter is tailored to provide you with the latest updates and insights about server-side Swift development. If you wish to opt out, simply click the unsubscribe link at the bottom of any email. <br />
            <br />
            Thank you for being a valued member of our community. If you have any questions or concerns regarding this update or anything else, please don't hesitate to reach out to us. We appreciate your continued support and look forward to keeping you informed and engaged with the swiftonserver.com newsletter.
          </mj-text>

          <mj-divider
            border-color="#DFE3E8"
            border-width="1px"
            padding="20px"
          />

          <mj-text
            color="#0095ff"
            font-weight="bold"
            font-size="20px"
            padding-bottom="0"
          >
            <a href="https://swiftonserver.com/whats-new-in-hummingbird-2/">What's new in Hummingbird 2?</a>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            The Hummingbird web-framework has undergone a big makeover! It's
            been released in an pre-release stage for a couple months now. This
            re-write of the framework aims to embrace structured concurrency,
            and is completely ready for <a href="https://forums.swift.org/t/swift-6-0-release-process/70220">Swift 6</a>. This article shows you what's
            changed!
          </mj-text>

          <mj-text
            color="#0095ff"
            font-weight="bold"
            font-size="20px"
            padding-bottom="0"
          >
            <a href="https://swiftpackageindex.com/lovetodream/oracle-nio">OracleNIO Database Driver Pitched</a>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            <a href="https://github.com/lovetodream">Timo Zacherl</a> has recently pitches their <a href="https://swiftpackageindex.com/lovetodream/oracle-nio">Oracle Database Driver</a> for incubation with the SSWG. Support for this database has been notoriously lacking, leaving many enterprise organisations unable to implement Server-Side Swift while keeping their preferred database.
          </mj-text>

          <mj-text
            color="#0095ff"
            font-weight="bold"
            font-size="20px"
            padding-bottom="0"
          >
            <a href="https://forums.swift.org/t/new-swift-package-repository-for-ubuntu-debian-linux-distributions/50412/177">Swift support for Amazon Linux 2023</a>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            Since Amazon has released Amazon Linux 2023 in March of last year, many users have been eager to see Swift support. This week <a href="https://github.com/futurejones">Neil Jones</a>, the maintainer of <a href="https://swiftlang.xyz">swiftlang.xyz</a>, has announced that they have <a href="https://github.com/futurejones/swift-arm64/releases/tag/amazon-linux-2023-dev">added support</a> for Swift on Amazon Linux 2023. In the same post, they've also announced an RPM repository for Swift.
          </mj-text>

          <mj-divider
            border-color="#DFE3E8"
            border-width="1px"
            padding="20px"
          />

          <mj-text
            color="#ff0095"
            font-weight="bold"
            font-size="20px"
            padding-bottom="0"
          >
            <a href="https://serversideswift.info">Swift Server Conference Announced</a>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            This week, Tim Condon <a href="https://twitter.com/SwiftServerConf/status/1762188533425422638">announced</a> that a new edition of the Server-Side Swift Conference. It's set to take place in the London Science Museum, and happening on September 26 &amp; 27. This annual event is a great opportunity to meet other Swift developers, and learn about the latest developments in the Server-Side Swift ecosystem.
          </mj-text>

          <mj-divider
            border-color="#DFE3E8"
            border-width="1px"
            padding="20px"
          />

          <mj-text
            color="#ff9500"
            font-weight="bold"
            font-size="20px"
            padding-bottom="0"
          >
            <a
              href="https://github.com/apple/swift-evolution/blob/main/proposals/0417-task-executor-preference.md"
              >Evolution: Task Executor Preferences</a
            >
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            Task executor preferences has been accepted in Swift Evolution! This
            new proposal allows frameworks such as Vapor and Hummingbird to run
            request handlers on a EventLoop. This allows for further performance
            optimisations across the ecosystem.
          </mj-text>

          <mj-divider
            border-color="#DFE3E8"
            border-width="1px"
            padding="20px"
          />

          <mj-text
            color="#00aa95"
            font-weight="bold"
            font-size="20px"
            padding-bottom="0"
          >
            <a
              href="https://swiftpackageindex.com/soto-project/soto"
              >Package Highlight: Soto</a
            >
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="16px">
            If you're using Swift on AWS, you probably already know this package! It's a great Swift SDK for anyone who needs to use one of AWS' many services, and pairs well with the <a href="https://swiftpackageindex.com/swift-server/swift-aws-lambda-runtime">Swift AWS Lambda Runtime</a>.
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>
      <mj-section background-color="#fcfcfc">
        <mj-column>
          <mj-text color="#637381" font-size="12px" align="center">
            <a href="https://unbeatable.software">Joannis Orlandos</a> &amp;
            <a href="https://binarybirds.com">Tibor BÃ¶decs</a>
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>
    </mj-wrapper>

    <mj-wrapper full-width="full-width">
      <mj-section>
        <mj-column width="100%" padding="0">
          <mj-text
            color="#445566"
            font-size="11px"
            align="center"
            line-height="16px"
          >
            You are receiving this email newsletter because you registered with
            the
            <a class="footer-link" href="https://swiftonserver.com"
              >swiftonserver.com</a
            >
            newsletter. <br />
            (previously
            <a class="footer-link" href="https://theswiftdev.com"
              >theswiftdev.com</a
            >
            newsletter)
          </mj-text>
        </mj-column>
      </mj-section>
